org.apache.commons.rdf.jena

Interface JenaGraph

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Graph, GraphLike<Triple>

    public interface JenaGraph
extends Graph
    A Jena-backed Graph.

    The underlying Jena Graph can be accessed with asJenaGraph().

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Graph asJenaGraph()
      Return the underlying Jena Graph.
      Model asJenaModel()
      Return the graph as a Jena Model.

      • Methods inherited from interface org.apache.commons.rdf.api.Graph

        add, add, clear, close, contains, contains, getTriples, getTriples, iterate, iterate, remove, remove, size, stream, stream

    • Method Detail

      • asJenaGraph

        Graph asJenaGraph()
        Return the underlying Jena Graph.

        Changes to the Jena graph are reflected in the Commons RDF graph and vice versa.

        Returns:
        A Jena Graph

      • asJenaModel

        Model asJenaModel()
        Return the graph as a Jena Model.

        Changes to the Jena model are reflected in the Commons RDF graph and vice versa.

        Note that in some cases there is no underlying Jena Model, in which case this method will create one. Subsequent calls should return the same model.

        Returns:
        A Jena Model
